The paper proposes a deep learning framework for image segmentation and landmarking, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed framework involves careful design of regularization and network hyper-parameters, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of a long short-term memory (LSTM) network is also mentioned, which is a type of recurrent neural network commonly used in natural language processing and time series analysis (cs.MS). Lastly, the paper deals with medical imaging data, which suggests a possible connection to multimedia (cs.MM).
